

Ruby on Rails Developer (Mid-Level)



Job Summary:

We are looking for a skilled Ruby on Rails Developer with 2+ years of experience to join our team. The ideal candidate should have a strong understanding of backend development using Ruby on Rails, experience working with databases, and the ability to collaborate with front-end developers and DevOps teams.


Key Responsibilities:

Develop, maintain, and optimize scalable web applications using Ruby on Rails.
Write clean, maintainable, and efficient code following best practices.
Design and manage database models and queries (PostgreSQL/MySQL).
Collaborate with front-end developers to integrate user-facing elements.
Implement and maintain APIs (RESTful & GraphQL).
Debug and troubleshoot issues to improve application performance.
Follow Agile methodologies and participate in sprint planning.
Work with DevOps to deploy and monitor applications in production.


Requirements:

2+ years of experience in Ruby on Rails development.
Strong understanding of MVC architecture and object-oriented programming.
Experience with PostgreSQL/MySQL and database optimization techniques.
Familiarity with frontend technologies (HTML, CSS, JavaScript) is a plus.
Experience with version control (Git/GitHub/GitLab).
Understanding of testing frameworks like RSpec or MiniTest.
Experience with Docker, CI/CD pipelines, and AWS is a plus.
Strong problem-solving skills and ability to work in a team.
